data.chText: 令人同情的；感人的；动人的
data.enText: causing feelings of pity or sympathy; making you feel emotional

data.chText: 那是一个让我们许多人落泪的动人故事。
data.enText: It was a touching story that moved many of us to tears.

simple_means.memory_skill: touch 摸，碰 + ing 令人…的 → 触及心灵 → 动人的

tr: the act of putting two things together with no space between them
example: at his touch the room filled with lights

tr: the event of something coming in contact with the body
example: he longed for the touch of her hand
the cooling touch of the night air
the homecoming of the released hostages was an affecting scene
his gratitude was simple and touching

value.def: If something is touching, it causes feelings of sadness or sympathy.

example.ex: Her story is the touching tale of a wife who stood by the husband she loved...
example.tran: 她的经历是一个妻子坚定地支持她深爱着的丈夫的感人故事。

example.ex: It was a very, very touching moment.
example.tran: 那是个非常非常感人的瞬间。

value.tran: 动人的;感人的;令人同情的

example.ex: He was touchingly naive about sex.

partsOfSpeech.dec: re 重新 + touch 摸，碰 → 重新用画笔接触画面 → 润色
touch 摸，碰 + ed 表形容词 → 触及心灵 → 受感动的
touch 摸，碰 + ing 正…的，令人…的 → 触及心灵 → 动人的
touch 摸，碰 + stone 石头 → 摸摸就知道是不是真金 → 试金石
touch 摸，碰 + y 多…的，有…的 → 一触即发的 → 易怒的
un 不 + touch 摸，碰 + able 可…的，能…的；具有…性质的 → 不可接触的
